('Pain after almost 5 years.', 'Dec 2014', 'patients wants to know if it\'s normal to experience pain 5 years after mastectomy and lymph node removal', 'patient had lymph nodes removal and a mastectomy ', 'not specified ', '', '', 'Many other patients report similar symptoms. They seem to be associated with inflamation following reconstruction procedures. Others also explain the pain by attributing it to the \"nerves growing bak together\"\"\"', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/827291', '', ''),
('Pain after almost 5 years.', 'December 31st, 2014', 'Pt continues to have \"sharp stabbing pains\"\" and feelings akin to \"\"creepy crawling\"\" under the skin 5 years after removal of problem lymph nodes and scar tissue. Wanted to know if that feeling is normal.\"', '', '', '', '', 'Other patients report same feeling of pain as well as tightness. As for an explanation, nerve growth was presented as a possible factor which is know to create muscle soreness.', 'Geon Kim', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/827291', '', ''),
