('PET Scan', 'Nov 2015', 'Patient wants to know if getting a PET scan at the begining of her treatment would be worth it', 'Carboplatin (Paraplatin), Taxotere (docetaxel) chemotherapy, Lumpectomy: Right; Lymph node removal: Sentinel, Underarm/Axillary', 'IDC, Right, 2cm, Stage IIA, Grade 2, 0/2 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2+ (FISH)', '', '', 'Many patients choose to get PET scans frequently just for peace of mind. Usually, physicians recomment getting a PET scan when new symptoms are present, to check if the cancer has spread. However, PET scans are not a substitute for other methods of scanning since they can show a false positive and only detect tumors 1cm or larger.', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/836936', '', ''),
