('Scan Anxiety!', 'Dec  2017', 'I need tips to overcome anxiety before CT scan ', 'patient has done chemotherapy, radiation, and hormonal therapy. She also had a sentinel lymph node removal and prophylactic mastectomy, followed by tissue expander placement reconstruction surgery ', 'IDC, Right, 2cm, Stage IIB, Grade 3, 1/4 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2-', 'Encouragement', '', 'Remember that youre not alone. Many patients feel the same anxiety and concern going for a scan. Scheduling your scan in advance may give you more time to be emotionally prepared. You can also try doing something you enjoy to help take your mind off of it. In case the anxiety was getting too severe that it interferes with your daily life, you can ask you physical for benzodiazepines such as Xanax to help relieve stress. ', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/860628', '', ''),
