('stomach swelling', 'May 2015', 'Patient is experiencing swelling in the stomach post surgery and wants to hear about similar patient experiences.a', 'Radical mastectomy on the left, and mastectomy on the right ', 'Stage IIB BC ', 'Side effect management', '', 'Definitely let your oncologist know about your condition. According to a similar patient experience, the stomach swelling could be due to anesthesia. The stomach remained swollen for about 3 weeks after the surgery. Drinking lots of water, using Miralax, and mostly eating fruits helped. ', 'Kriti Bhardwaj, Amira Elfergani', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/831211', '', ''),
('Surgery?', 'Jan 2019 ', 'I needs help determining whetehr to get a lumpectomy or a double mastectomy ', 'chemotherapy (AC +T)', 'not given ', '', '', 'the following site offers a list of considerations for someone making the surgical choice: https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/91/topics/868997?page=1#post_5329372', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/869351', '', ''),
