('swelling of both feet a concern', 'July 2015', 'Patient had to get her implants removed after her breast expanders got infected. Now she is on zoladex and tamoxifen and is worried about the swelling and pain in her feet. ', 'Bilateral mastectomy followed by radiation, positive lymph node ', 'Stage II BC ', 'Side effect management', '', 'Tamoxifen does cause joint pain but swelling and pain in feet can be counted as brutal side effects. It is best to let your doctor know so that a different medicine can be prescribed.  ', 'Kriti Bhardwaj ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/833671', '', ''),
('Symptoms of cancer spreading !!!!', 'October 2016', 'Patient has cancer with moderate growth and is experiencing pain in hips and the healthy breast. According to the doctor, it is just in her head as it is way too early for her to experience symptoms of metastasis. PET scan results showed that patient was fine but she wants to know if this information is enough to clear her doubts. ', 'Chemotherapy AC + T (Taxol), Hormonal Therapy (Arimidex), Radiation Therapy (Whole-breast)', 'IDC, right, 2cm, stage IIA, grade 3, 1/19 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2-', 'Symptom diagnosis', '', 'When concerned about experiencing any pain or symptoms, it is best to check with the doctor. Also, getting a PET scan clears all doubts about metastasis. If both confirm that there is no metastasis, it is possible that worrying or stress might be causing the pain. Injury, sleeping wrong, pinched back nerve etc. can be the reasons behind the pain. \n Having undiagnosed pain might not be related to the breast cancer but that does not mean that it does not require medical attention. Seeing an orthopedist and getting an MRI scan done can help. \n', 'Kriti Bhardwaj ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/849267', '', ''),
