('Telling friends at work about your diagnosis', 'January 2018 ', 'Patients wants to know when and how to tell cowrokers about her diagnosis ', 'Lymph node removal: Sentinel; Mastectomy: Right; Reconstruction (right): Silicone implant', 'DCIS/IDC, Right, Grade 3, 0/3 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2- (FISH)', 'Other/ Miscellaneous', '', 'It might be helpful to delay telling coworkers about your diagnosis until you have had time to deal with your own feelings and thoughts. People might feel the need to constantly ask questions about you diagnosis and treatment; which will add extra pressure to you. However, only telling your close friends can actually be very helpful in finding support and reassurance.', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/861498', '', ''),
('Thanks and HUMBLED', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/824516', '', ''),
('The doc said what?', 'Sep 2015 ', 'patient was offended by doctor\'s remarks that show lack of compassion', 'Lymph node removal, breast reconstruction, lumpectomy, hormonal therapy ', 'Stage 2A; IDC: Mucinous, Right, 2cm, 0/2 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2-', 'Other/Miscellaneous', '', 'Try to address any concerns directly with your physician; especially, if they affect your personal welling. You might save another more vulnerable person from even worse results by helping your doctor realize the impact of her words. ', 'Amira Elfergani ', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/834990', '', ''),
