('tired and scared', 'Dec 15 2014', 'Patient feels weak and has high recurrence risk. Extensive chemo treatment exhausted the patient. She refused further treatment as a result. Wants to hear about similar experiences. ', 'Lumpectomy (right), Chemotherapy (CEF), no radiation', 'IDC, 2cm, Stage II, Grade 2, 0/3 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2-', 'Encouragement', '', 'Patient might have depression and should look into getting that treated separately. Another thing said was that feeling anger is perfectly normal in response to this disease, especially if a previous doctor did a poor job of diagnosing it. Tiredness might also be due to anemia is one thing that was mentioned.', 'Devansh Dwivedy', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/826993', '', ''),
