('Worried about making decision......', 'January 2015', 'Patient\'s oncologist has recommended her to just take Tamoxifen as treatment for 2-3 years. The patient wants to know if taking Tamoxifen is enough as a treatment and if not doing chemotherapy is okay?  ', 'Mastectomy: Left; Prophylactic mastectomy: Right, Hormonal Therapy, Prophylactic ovary removal, oncotype score is 6, recurrence rate is 5%', 'Stage 2A, grade 2 ILC, 0/4 nodes, ER+/PR+, HER2-', 'Right treatment?', '', 'Chemotherapy can cause serious side effects that can affect things like your ability to type and do math. Therefore, if chemotherapy is not needed, it should be avoided. A low oncotype score shows that the cancer has a low chance of recurrence and it will not respond well to chemotherapy. ', 'Preetham Ramesh', 'https://community.breastcancer.org/forum/145/topics/827354', '', '');
